---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Accessibility - telMAX"
  description="telMAX is committed to digital accessibility and to meeting its obligations under the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA)."
>
  <section class="section bg-green hero-block">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-block__inner">
        <span class="pill">Accessibility</span>
        <h1>Accessibility at telMAX</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="prose">
        <p class="updated">Last reviewed: July 2026</p>
        <p>
          telMAX is committed to making our services and our website usable by
          everyone, including people with disabilities. This statement is
          provided as a starting template - please have it reviewed by qualified
          counsel and confirmed against your current practices before publishing.
        </p>

        <h2>Our commitment</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to meet or exceed the accessibility requirements of the
          Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA) and its
          Integrated Accessibility Standards Regulation, and we use the Web
          Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA as our design
          benchmark.
        </p>

        <h2>What we do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Design pages that work with keyboard navigation and screen readers.</li>
          <li>Maintain clear colour contrast, visible focus states and readable text.</li>
          <li>Respect the "reduce motion" setting for animations and transitions.</li>
          <li>Provide meaningful text alternatives for images and controls.</li>
          <li>Review new features for accessibility as part of our ongoing work.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Accessible formats and support</h2>
        <p>
          If you need information from telMAX in an accessible format, or you
          require support to use our services, we will work with you to provide it
          in a suitable format and in a reasonable time, at no additional cost.
        </p>

        <h2>Accessible customer service</h2>
        <p>
          Our support team is trained to assist customers with disabilities. If
          you use an assistive device, service animal or support person, you are
          welcome to do so when interacting with telMAX.
        </p>

        <h2>Give us feedback</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website and
          services - it helps us improve. Please contact us and let us know if you
          encounter a barrier:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email <a href="mailto:support@telmax.com" style="text-decoration:underline">support@telmax.com</a></li>
          <li>Call <a href="tel:18444835629" style="text-decoration:underline">1-844-483-5629</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within one business day and
          to resolve issues as quickly as we can.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-block { padding-top: clamp(64px, 9vw, 120px); }
</style>
